AstrOsEspNowPeers
=================

Pure, native-testable peer list for the ESP-NOW adapter. Owns the
vector of registered padawan peers and the per-cycle pollAck flag
lifecycle (resetPollCycle / markPollAckReceived / listUnacked).

AstrOsEspNow (MIXED) wraps PeerList with its peersMutex so every
access is serialised; the class itself has no locks. Fixes the
"unprotected peers vector" finding from the April 2026 code review
by making the vector unreachable except via PeerList methods.

Purity rule
-----------

This library is unit-tested on the native host under [env:test], so it
must not include any of:

    freertos/*, esp_*, driver/*, nvs_*, sdmmc_*, esp_vfs*, esp_now*, esp_wifi*

Enforced by the CI purity guard in .github/workflows/pr-validation.yml.

Error-channel convention
------------------------

Methods return enum values (AddResult), std::optional, or booleans.
No logging. The MIXED adapter (AstrOsEspNow) logs at the boundary if
a call returns a non-success outcome.
